	title Box-js: a tool for studying JavaScript malware
body.container
	.text-xs-center
		h1 Box-js
		h4 A tool for studying JavaScript malware
	h3 Main features
	ul
		li.
			Emulation of #[b ActiveX components]: #[tt MSXML2.XMLHTTP], #[tt WScript.Shell], #[tt ADODB.Stream], #[tt Scripting.FileSystemObject]
		li.
			Suitable for #[b integration and automation]: creates a JSON file with active URLs for easy scripting
		li.
			#[b Secure]: runs code in a #[a(href="https://nodejs.org/api/vm.html") V8 sandbox] which doesn't expose system APIs
	h3 Usage
	h4 Installing
	pre: b.
		$ curl -sL https://deb.nodesource.com/setup_7.x | sudo -E bash -
		$ sudo apt-get install nodejs npm
		$ npm install --global box-js
	h4 Analysing
	pre.
		<b>$ box-js sample.js --download --no-kill --timeout=60</b>
